Defendant Quintin J. Armbrust in court, in custody with attorney Alexander Paul Seifert.  Elizabeth R. Constable appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court calls 14CF193, 15CM61 & 16CM110  @ 3:09  pm. State gives plea agreement, 184 days credit, State received revocation summary packet, no corrections.  3-6 months jail on 14CF193 and 3 months 15CM61. 16CM110 ct 2 DRI, Ct plea 30 days jail consecutive, costs.   Atty Seifert agrees with agreement.  Atty Seifert received revocation summary packet, no corrections.  Plea questionnaire and waiver of rights filed.  Def. understand charge and penalties. Ct 1 Failure to report to jail, no contest plea. Ct 2 DRI. Def. advised of constitutional rights & J.T. rights.  Def. understands elements.  Atty Seifert is satisfied.  Court finds plea is freely & voluntarily given.  Factual basis stipulated.  Court finds factual basis, accepts plea and finds def. Guilty to Failure to report to Jail. State gives sentencing recommendation.  Atty Seifert gives sentencing recommendation.  Def. has nothing to say.  Court orders
14CF193 ct 1 6 months jail, 
Ct 3 30 days jail, concurrent to ct 1
15CM61 30 days jail, concurrent to 14CF193
Court costs converted to civil judgment. 184 days credit, served.
16CM110 - Ct 1- 30 days jail, consecutive to other sentences. Credit from other cases, Time served, so probably completed, 200 DNA Surcharge, costs. Def. given p.p. $50 a month 1st payment due 2-1-17. Huber privileges.  Def. advised of postconviction rights.

Defendant Quintin J. Armbrust in court with attorney Brent Harold Debord.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 14CF193 and 15CM61 @ 9:31 a.m. Off the record 9:32. Back on the record 9:32. Agreement stated - 14-CF-193 - Def will plead to Ct 1 amended to simple possession of THC 961.41(3g)(e) 939.05, and to ct 3, ct 2 dismissed. Ct 1 withheld sentence, 2 yrs probation, AODA and other counsel deemed appropriate, court costs, 30 days jail w/60 days to report. Ct 3 withheld sentence, 1 yr probation, cc. 15CM61 - withheld sentence, 1 yr probation, counseling, costs including DNA surcharge and sample. Atty Debord agrees, 84 days credit if revoked. Def agrees. Plea quest. reviewed. Court grants motion to amend ct 1 to simple possession of THC PTAC. Plea to 14-CF-193 ct 1 - no contest. ct 3 - no contest plea. 15CM61 ct 1 - no contest plea. 14CF193 ct 2 dismissed. Constitutional rights, elements and possible penalties reviewed. Off the record briefly. Back on the record. Atty Debord satisfied. Court finds Def understands and pleas freely & voluntarily made. Factual basis. Court accepts pleas and finds guilty of 14CF193 ct 1 as amended, and ct 3 possess drug paraphernalia, ptac, and 15CM61 possess of drug paraphernalia. Sentencing remarks by Counsel. Nothing by Defendant. Sentencing remarks by the Court. Court approves agreement. 14CF193 ct 1 - sentence withheld, 2 yrs probation, AODA and follow through as required, court costs, 30 days jail, report no later than 6 p.m. on 1/8/16, huber. 84 days credit if revoked. Ct 3- sentence withheld, 1 yr probation, court costs, same conditions as ct 1. 15CM61 ct 1 - withheld sentence, 1 yr probation, same conditions, court costs, DNA sample and surcharge.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. Postconviction rights. (Clarified with Judge - jail is only on ct 1 of 14CF193)
